        "locked": false,
        "title": "Left/right provider navigation doesn't work",
        "body": "## Description\n\nIn CodexBar `0.29.1`, the merged provider switcher has left/right arrow navigation in the code, but it does not work for me in the actual open menu.\n\nThis is separate from #1144. Cmd-number shortcuts would be new shortcuts, while this is existing left/right navigation code that does not seem to work through the real menu.\n\n## Environment\n\n- CodexBar version: `0.29.1`\n- Base/source context: current `main` after `v0.29.1` still has the same left/right navigation path\n- macOS version: `26.5 (25F71)`\n- Hardware: Apple Silicon (`MacBookPro17,1`)\n- Menu mode: merged provider switcher menu\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Enable merged icon mode with multiple providers\n2. Open the CodexBar menu from the menu bar\n3. Press the right arrow key\n4. Press the left arrow key\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nNothing changes in the provider switcher.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n- right arrow moves to the next switcher item\n- left arrow moves to the previous switcher item\n\n## Reproducibility\n\nThis is reproducible on my machine.\n\nI verified:\n\n- the provider switcher is visible at the top of the open menu\n- clicking the provider switcher works\n- pressing left/right while the menu is open does not switch providers\n\n## Evidence\n\nThe code already appears to have left/right provider switcher navigation, but the existing test path calls `performKeyEquivalent` directly. That does not prove the real open `NSMenu` receives left/right keypresses.",
